<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>MOR/RYDE RUBBER SPRING SUSPENSION - REPLACEMENT - BEAM ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="1">
        <title>BEAM ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The beam assembly supports one side of the rubber springs forward and rearward of the axle and is
                located on the axle in the same position the steel leaf springs would have been (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0300908">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0300908" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300908" filename="../figg03/G0300908.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. BEAM ASSEMBLY ATTACHMENT TO AXLE HOUSING</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.U-BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.BOLT, .75-10 X 3.50 (ALLEN HEAD)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.AXLE PAD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.AXLE HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>5.BOTTOM U-BOLT CASTING</callout1>
                    <callout1>6.U-BOLT NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>7.BEAM ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The beam assembly is attached to the axle through U-bolts. The proper torquing procedure in attaching
                the beam assembly to the axle is
                <emph type="bold">extremely</emph>
                important to suspension reliability.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure vehicle is elevated, the chassis is supported with safety stands, the front
                    wheels blocked, and the suspension hanging unsupported.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove tires and rims from the drive axle on side of vehicle to be repaired. Refer to
                    GROUP 17 - WHEELS, TIRES AND RIMS in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Support axle housing with floor jack.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove shock absorbers. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s03009_11.xml" xrefid="hl0300904">SHOCK ABSORBER</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove rubber spring assemblies from beam assembly. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s03009_6.xml" xrefid="hl0300905">RUBBER SPRINGS</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove U-bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0300908">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove beam assembly from axle.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure axle pad assembly with round or oblong pin is set on axle seat before
                    installing new beam.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place new beam assembly on axle pad assembly using new U-bolts and nuts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten U-bolt nuts to 50 ft-lbs. (68 N&#8226;m).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten leveling bolt on side of beam into axle pad adjustment seat. Tighten to 75
                    ft-lbs. (102 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten U-bolt nuts following tightening sequence (
                    <hotlnk document="s03009_2.xml" xrefid="f0300902">Figure 2</hotlnk>) until final torque is achieved.
                    Refer to the
                    <hotlnk document="s03009_12.xml" xrefid="hl0300901">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reinstall rubber spring assemblies. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s03009_6.xml" xrefid="hl0300905">RUBBER SPRINGS</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
